                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "I see there's no delay between requests when prefetching or on rate limit. Looking at the chat history again, there was a discussion about adding delays but I need to verify if it's in the code:\n\nBased on my analysis, here's the situation:\n\n## Summary\n\n**The rate limiting issue is caused by:**\n1. **YouTube API rate limits** - Your Poco and emulator share the same public IP, but the emulator's requests have a different TLS fingerprint that YouTube's rate limiter treats differently\n2. **No backoff delay** - The current code tries multiple clients in parallel but doesn't wait between retries after a rate limit\n\n**Solutions already in place:**\n- Stream URL caching (survives app restarts)\n- Multiple client fallbacks\n- Server-side URL fetching (when available)\n- Rate limit detection with `YouTubeRateLimitException`\n\n**What's missing:**\n- A delay/backoff when rate-limited before retrying\n- The server doesn't yet provide `GET /songs/:id/stream-url` endpoint to bypass YouTube entirely\n\n**Quick test to confirm it's IP-based rate limiting:**\n1. Wait 5-10 minutes without using the app\n2. Try again - if songs play, it was a temporary rate limit\n3. If still failing, try on mobile data (different IP) - if it works, confirms IP-based throttling\n\nWould you like me to:\n1. Add a retry delay when rate-limited?\n2. Add exponential backoff for the `getAudioUrl` method?\n3. Something else?"
