content.data:
Found it. In `send()`:
```dart
headers.forEach((key, value) {
  if (request.headers[key] == null) {  // only sets if NOT already present
    request.headers[key] = headers[key]!;
  }
});
```

`headers` returns `defaultHeaders` which has `'cookie': 'CONSENT=YES+cb'`. Since `cookie` is already set by `defaultHeaders`, our `CookieHttpClient` sets `Cookie` (capital C) but `YoutubeHttpClient.send()` checks for `cookie` (lowercase). The header merge uses `defaultHeaders` which already has `cookie` set — so our cookie never gets applied because the key check is case-sensitive and `defaultHeaders` already has `cookie`.

The fix: subclass `YoutubeHttpClient` and override `headers` to include our cookies:

